comments:
Absorption measurements by photographic photometry, the light sources used were a "Pointolite" for the visible, a mercury arc lamp for the visible and near ultra-violet, a tungsten-steel
spark and an aluminium spark for the far ultra-violet
name: hydrogen selenide
